  "body": "<!-- **Are you in the right place?**\r\n1. For issues or feature requests, please create an issue in this repository.\r\n2. For general technical and non-technical questions, we are happy to help you on our [Rook.io Slack](https://slack.rook.io/).\r\n3. Did you already search the existing open issues for anything similar? -->\r\n\r\n**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Deviation from expected behavior:**\r\nWith #5091 rgw metadata pool are created with 8 pgs by default based on rgw_rados_pool_pg_num_min parameter.\r\nBut with pg_autoscaler plugin activated the autoscaler immediately increase the size of those pool to it default PG_NUM_MIN of 32.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nIn order to avoid this rook should set pg_num_min on those pool to the value of rgw_rados_pool_pg_num_min\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\n\r\n- Create a cluster on v14.2.8 or newer\r\n- Activate pg atoscaer plugin\r\n- Create a ceph object store\r\n- Check number of pgs per metadata pool (should be 32)\r\n",
